This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. The paper proposes a new approach for aspect-level sentiment classification using constrained attention networks. This topic is closely related to other sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are also likely categories for this paper. Additionally, the paper involves regularization techniques, which are commonly used in optimization problems, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could make cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
